# Fantasy Baseball Agent — Environment

## Python Environment

- **Python Executable**: `{{PYTHON_EXECUTABLE}}`
- **Package Root**: `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}`
- **Install Command**: `pip install -e .` (run once from the package root)
- **CLI**: `fba daily | weekly | trade-scan | draft-prep`

## Data Paths

| Path | Contents |
|------|----------|
| `data/raw/` | Raw ESPN and MLB API outputs (CSV, JSON) |
| `data/processed/` | Derived analysis outputs |
| `reports/` | Weekly prep and trade scan markdown reports |
| `logs/` | JSONL run logs (one file per workflow/script) |
| `config.ini` | Credentials and LLM provider settings (never commit) |

## LLM Configuration

The `agent/llm/` module supports four providers. Set the active one in `config.ini`:

```ini
[llm]
provider = anthropic    # anthropic | google | openai | ollama
model    = claude-sonnet-4-6
```

See `CREDENTIALS_GUIDE.md` for ESPN cookie setup and `config.ini.example` for the full config schema.

