## Your Coding Standards

<!-- Fill in your own rules below. The section above is fixed project structure. -->
<!-- These guidelines apply to any code you write or edit in this project.      -->

- Never use `pandas` in final artifacts or reusable module code
- Never hardcode credentials — read from `config.ini` via `configparser`
- All `.py` files must have a module docstring with **Description**, **Source Data**, and **Outputs** headers
- Data file naming: `{Category}_{Source}_{Granularity}_{TimePeriod}.{ext}` (see `CONVENTIONS.md`)
- Script naming: `{Verb}_{Object}_{Source}_{Modifier}.py`

